<p>This is a placeholder piece in the Reading Room. The goal is to validate reading ergonomics: line length, rhythm, spacing, and distraction level.</p>

<h2>On noticing</h2>
<p>Notice is not the same as admire. Notice is precise: where did the line turn? What did it refuse to explain? What did it make you supply?</p>

<h2>On saving</h2>
<p>Snippets are a commonplace book. They’re not a trophy cabinet. Save what you can re-use as a move: a cadence, a pressure, a cut.</p>
